column5: I moved to Innisfil and discovered my garage isn't as big as  I thunk it was  so now I am looking for year round indoor storage  my skidoo/atv in the summer and my boat in the winter I don't need heated the closer to innisfil the better but price is more important then being close  does anyone know of ant good deals  thanks
If it was summer storage for the boat and winter storage for the atv and ski-doo I wouldn't even charge rent to keep the stuff at my place.
yeah, that would work...lol for a minute I thought I suffered from Dyslexia
You mean I might have had a shot? I should have worked on my proposal a little more.
eh no  I thought maybe I wrote the wrong thing in my first post, but a quick look cleared that up  you had no chance..  but 20 points for effort
You can store them at my house for free.......   Art
Well Terry.. you know, if you're stuck, where the sled and trailer can go for the summer.
thanks Wayne I really  really am hoping to find something there must be barns or something around........
Go for a drive, most farmers are pretty nice guys and like cheques. Maybe your local sled' atv dealer has a spot or knows someone who does.

Barns are a great place to store toys Terry, I used one for my boat for about 9 years. If you do go that route though, just be sure you'll be able to get your stuff out when you want it. I knew the other guys who shared the barn with me so it was never an issue, but if your things are blocked by others you could have a problem.  Just something to think about.
Shouldn't be too hard to find a barn around Innisfil
Guess I will start knocking on doors.
